ction\":\"verse_text\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.verse-text\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":3480,\"bb\":3066,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3066/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003earjuna uvāca\u003cbr /\u003eevaṁ satata-yuktā ye\u003cbr /\u003ebhaktās tvāṁ paryupāsate\u003cbr /\u003eye cāpy akṣaram avyaktaṁ\u003cbr /\u003eteṣāṁ ke yoga-vittamāḥ\u003c/em\u003e\"}]},{\"section\":\"synonyms\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.synonyms\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"books.Synonyms\",\"title\":\"synonyms\",\"id\":3481,\"bb\":3067,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3067/\",\"shadow_value\":\"\u003cem\u003earjunaḥ uvāca\u003c/em\u003e – Arjuna said; \u003cem\u003eevam\u003c/em\u003e – thus; \u003cem\u003esatata\u003c/em\u003e – always; \u003cem\u003eyuktāḥ\u003c/em\u003e – engaged; \u003cem\u003eye\u003c/em\u003e – those who; \u003cem\u003ebhaktāḥ\u003c/em\u003e – devotees; \u003cem\u003etvām\u003c/em\u003e – You; \u003cem\u003eparyupāsate\u003c/em\u003e – properly worship; \u003cem\u003eye\u003c/em\u003e – those who; \u003cem\u003eca\u003c/em\u003e – also; \u003cem\u003eapi\u003c/em\u003e – again; \u003cem\u003eakṣaram\u003c/em\u003e – beyond the senses; \u003cem\u003eavyaktam\u003c/em\u003e – the unmanifested; \u003cem\u003eteṣām\u003c/em\u003e – of them; \u003cem\u003eke\u003c/em\u003e – who; \u003cem\u003eyoga-vit-tamāḥ\u003c/em\u003e – the most perfect in knowledge of \u003cem\u003eyoga.\u003c/em\u003e\",\"word_for_word_value\":[{\"word\":\"arjunaḥ uvāca\",\"translation\":\"Arjuna said\"},{\"word\":\"evam\",\"translation\":\"thus\"},{\"word\":\"satata\",\"translation\":\"always\"},{\"word\":\"yuktāḥ\",\"translation\":\"engaged\"},{\"word\":\"ye\",\"translation\":\"those who\"},{\"word\":\"bhaktāḥ\",\"translation\":\"devotees\"},{\"word\":\"tvām\",\"translation\":\"You\"},{\"word\":\"paryupāsate\",\"translation\":\"properly worship\"},{\"word\":\"ye\",\"translation\":\"those who\"},{\"word\":\"ca\",\"translation\":\"also\"},{\"word\":\"api\",\"translation\":\"again\"},{\"word\":\"akṣaram\",\"translation\":\"beyond the senses\"},{\"word\":\"avyaktam\",\"translation\":\"the unmanifested\"},{\"word\":\"teṣām\",\"translation\":\"of them\"},{\"word\":\"ke\",\"translation\":\"who\"},{\"word\":\"yoga-vit-tamāḥ\",\"translation\":\"the most perfect in knowledge of \u003cem\u003eyoga.\u003c/em\u003e\"}]}]},{\"section\":\"translation\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.translation\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"translation\",\"id\":3482,\"bb\":3068,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3068/\",\"body_value\":\"Arjuna inquired: Which are considered to be more perfect, those who are always properly engaged in Your devotional service or those who worship the impersonal Brahman, the unmanifested?\"}]},{\"section\":\"purport\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.purport\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3483,\"bb\":3069,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3069/\",\"body_value\":\"Kṛṣṇa has now explained about the personal, the impersonal and the universal and has described all kinds of devotees and \u003cem\u003eyogīs\u003c/em\u003e. Generally, the transcendentalists can be divided into two classes. One is the impersonalist, and the other is the personalist. The personalist devotee engages himself with all energy in the service of the Supreme Lord. The impersonalist also engages himself, not directly in the service of Kṛṣṇa but in meditation on the impersonal Brahman, the unmanifested.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3484,\"bb\":3070,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3070/\",\"body_value\":\"We find in this chapter that of the different processes for realization of the Absolute Truth, \u003cem\u003ebhakti-yoga,\u003c/em\u003e devotional service, is the highest. If one at all desires to have the association of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, then he must take to devotional service.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3485,\"bb\":3071,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3071/\",\"body_value\":\"Those who worship the Supreme Lord directly by devotional service are called personalists. Those who engage themselves in meditation on the impersonal Brahman are called impersonalists. Arjuna is here questioning which position is better. There are different ways to realize the Absolute Truth, but Kṛṣṇa indicates in this chapter that \u003cem\u003ebhakti-yoga,\u003c/em\u003e or devotional service to Him, is the highest of all. It is the most direct, and it is the easiest means for association with the Godhead.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3486,\"bb\":3072,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3072/\",\"body_value\":\"In the Second Chapter of \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā,\u003c/em\u003e the Supreme Lord explained that a living entity is not the material body; he is a spiritual spark. And the Absolute Truth is the spiritual whole. In the Seventh Chapter He spoke of the living entity as being part and parcel of the supreme whole and recommended that he transfer his attention fully to the whole. Then again in the Eighth Chapter it was said that anyone who thinks of Kṛṣṇa at the time of quitting his body is at once transferred to the spiritual sky, to the abode of Kṛṣṇa. And at the end of the Sixth Chapter the Lord clearly said that of all \u003cem\u003eyogīs,\u003c/em\u003e one who always thinks of Kṛṣṇa within himself is considered the most perfect. So in practically every chapter the conclusion has been that one should be attached to the personal form of Kṛṣṇa, for that is the highest spiritual realization.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3487,\"bb\":3073,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3073/\",\"body_value\":\"Nevertheless, there are those who are not attached to the personal form of Kṛṣṇa. They are so firmly detached that even in the preparation of commentaries to \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā\u003c/em\u003e they want to distract other people from Kṛṣṇa and transfer all devotion to the impersonal \u003cem\u003ebrahma-jyotir\u003c/em\u003e. They prefer to meditate on the impersonal form of the Absolute Truth, which is beyond the reach of the senses and is not manifest.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":3488,\"bb\":3074,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/1/b3074/\",\"body_value\":\"$2d\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 12.1\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 12.1\"},{\"id\":3489,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"2\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 2\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/advanced-view/#bb3075\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti keel (Estonian)\",\"language_code\":\"et\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/et/library/bg/12/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Suomen kieli (Finnish)\",\"language_code\":\"fi\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/fi/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Français (French)\",\"language_code\":\"fr\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/fr/library/bg/12